S. Africa Isn’t Opposed to Foreign Investment, Bus. Day Says

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-04-05T05:13:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/south-africa-isn-t-opposed-to-foreign-investment-business-day-reports.html
  South Africa  isn’t opposed to
foreign investment, Lionel October, the acting director-general
of the country’s trade ministry, said after it intervened in
competition hearings over planned takeovers by  Wal-Mart Stores
Inc. (WMT)  and Kansai Paint Co., Business Day Reported  The planned takeover of Johannesburg-based  Massmart
Holdings Ltd. (MSM)  and by Bentonville, Arkansas-based Wal-Mart could
expose South African industry to low-cost Chinese goods while
 Japan ’s Kansai planned to takeover unique technology owned by
 Freeworld Coatings Ltd. (FWD) , he said, according to the Johannesburg-
based newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  